<br>
One thing that was especially memorable to me (maybe due to how late in the movie it was of course), was the booming voice of the machine &quot;leader&quot; or whatever it was.  When the theatre floor and my chest shakes, it's all good IMO.  If I knew I wasn't going to buy it on DVD when it came out anyway, I'd probably see it many more times in the theatre.  I'm a big movie soundtrack fan, and from what I heard this soundtrack was pretty fucking kick ass; definitely going to be picking that up soon.<br>
<br>
However, if you want to know what is boring and stupid to me, it's all the needledicks who, instead of going to a movie to watch a work of fiction and be *entertained*, are only looking for more fuel to burn in their message board flames.  God, I wouldnt have had any fun either if the only thing I was doing there was constantly figuring out why every scene was fucking stupid or impossible or too long or not what I would have created or didnt tell exactly what I wanted told or one of 1000 other nonsensical complaints.  <br>
<br>
Why do people actually think they are doing something important or special or even remotely fucking interesting when they're tearing down something that is harmless and was created purely for entertainment?  (This post ends up arguing against its own existance, damnit)<br>
