<br>
The Bros. Wachowski's dialogue skills hava taken a beating, somehow.  Or perhaps they were never any good, or were not-any-good in a way that was better suited to the small truths of the first film than the large Truths of the later ones.  And the first one, which struck me at the time as heavily derivative of many things, particularly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Dark City</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, did have one thing going for it: vastly superior pacing.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is that it's not as good a movie as <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bubbahotep.com">BUBBA HO-TEP</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (prepare to be blown away by the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.apple.com/trailers/independent/bubba_ho-tep/">trailer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->),<br>
and that movie probably isn't even playing in your city, let alone on forty screens.<br>
